This paper deals with optimization algorithms for large-scale machine learning problems, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses asynchronous optimization algorithms, which are commonly used in distributed computing, so cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also mentions experiments and numerical analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the paper deals with optimization of composite functions, which is a topic in optimization theory, so cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new method for optimization, which could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
